    {
      "id": "1b34750c-f3ba-80b2-8789-dcbb984c1587",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "The first representation is Co-occurrence representation learning which follow a random-walk and skip-grams to identify meta-paths. The second representation is semantic-aware representation learning. Both are combined to be fed as input to a matrix factorization algorithm. The approach is tested on multiple public datasets with other HIN recommenders.   ",
      "raw": {
        "object": "block",
        "id": "1b34750c-f3ba-80b2-8789-dcbb984c1587",
        "parent": {
          "type": "page_id",
